{"pagelen": 100, "values": [{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/2846/comments/53031619.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/2846/_/diff#comment-53031619"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 2846, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/2846.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/2846"}}, "title": "Rename `BUILD_TYPE_*` macros to `GAZEBO_BUILD_TYPE_*` (issue #2343)"}, "content": {"raw": "Strictly speaking, deprecation can be done using [this suggestion](#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/2840/move-build_type_-macros-to-test_configh/diff#comment-52849973), but it's not exactly pretty, and probably not worthwhile.\n\nI would suggest we put a note in `cmake/gazebo_config.h.in` above the macros to indicate that they will be removed in the future and should not be used. In general, they aren't a reliable method for identifying the build type anyway (installing more than one build type at a time will corrupt the macro values).", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Strictly speaking, deprecation can be done using <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/2840/move-build_type_-macros-to-test_configh/diff#comment-52849973\" rel=\"nofollow\">this suggestion</a>, but it's not exactly pretty, and probably not worthwhile.</p>\n<p>I would suggest we put a note in <code>cmake/gazebo_config.h.in</code> above the macros to indicate that they will be removed in the future and should not be used. In general, they aren't a reliable method for identifying the build type anyway (installing more than one build type at a time will corrupt the macro values).</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-01-05T02:25:42.736492+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Michael Grey", "uuid": "{c1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9%7D"}, "html": {"hr